  "gold_answer": "3",
  "generated_text": "To find the total number of bolts of fiber required, we need to add the amount of blue fiber and the amount of white fiber together.\n\n1.  **Identify the amount of blue fiber:**\n    The problem states that the robe takes 2 bolts of blue fiber.\n\n2.  **Calculate the amount of white fiber:**\n    The problem states that the white fiber is \"half that much\" as the blue fiber.\n    $$ \\text{White fiber} = \\frac{1}{2} \\times 2 = 1 \\text{ bolt} $$\n\n3.  **Calculate the total number of bolts:**\n    Add the blue and white bolts together.\n    $$ \\text{Total bolts} = \\text{Blue bolts} + \\text{White bolts} $$\n    $$ \\text{Total bolts} = 2 + 1 = 3 $$\n\nThe total number of bolts required is 3.\n\n\\boxed{3}\n",
